00:00:22,623 --> 00:00:26,025
narrator: today, on "how it's made"...   

4
00:00:26,027 --> 00:00:27,994
l.e.d. stage lights...      

5
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:33,866
...apple cider...        

6
00:00:38,373 --> 00:00:39,805
...chemical tank trailers...   

7
00:00:43,845 --> 00:00:46,379
...and ornate stone floors.   

8
00:00:53,654 --> 00:00:55,654
in the world of stage lighting,            

9
00:00:55,656 --> 00:00:58,991
traditional incandescent or halogen bulb spotlights    

10
00:00:58,993 --> 00:01:01,660
are making way for l.e.d.s.   

11
00:01:01,662 --> 00:01:03,929
l.e.d.s are light-emitting diodes      

12
00:01:03,931 --> 00:01:05,631
controlled by electronics.    

13
00:01:05,633 --> 00:01:08,267
they use less energy, emit less heat,         

14
00:01:08,269 --> 00:01:10,269
and can produce a wide array of colors            

15
00:01:10,271 --> 00:01:13,739
without the use of filters.   

16
00:01:13,741 --> 00:01:17,209
incandescent or halogen stage  
lights produce just one color.  

17
00:01:17,211 --> 00:01:20,279
the only way to create more is to shine the light beam              

18
00:01:20,281 --> 00:01:23,281
through colored plastic called gel filters.       

19
00:01:23,283 --> 00:01:25,284
however, this l.e.d. stage light              

20
00:01:25,286 --> 00:01:27,886
uses seven different colored l.e.d.s,         

21
00:01:27,888 --> 00:01:31,757
which can be blended into a variety of different hues.   

22
00:01:31,759 --> 00:01:36,696
this computer-guided machine places all the components    

23
00:01:36,698 --> 00:01:38,497
on the stage light's circuit board,          

24
00:01:38,499 --> 00:01:42,835
which contains 60 l.e.d.s in 7 different base colors.   

25
00:01:51,846 --> 00:01:53,179
another machine measures     

26
00:01:53,181 --> 00:01:56,282
and cuts pieces of insulated electrical wire.  

27
00:02:00,121 --> 00:02:03,389
then, the machine strips the insulation off the ends   

28
00:02:03,391 --> 00:02:05,491
and crimps on terminals.     

29
00:02:07,462 --> 00:02:11,430
the machine processes up    
to 26 feet of wire per second.  

30
00:02:14,468 --> 00:02:17,736
workers manually assemble 10 wires and two connectors   

31
00:02:17,738 --> 00:02:19,805
into a control harness.     

32
00:02:19,807 --> 00:02:22,074
the harness will connect the light's control board    

33
00:02:22,076 --> 00:02:24,076
to the l.e.d. array.       

34
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:27,680
on the factory floor,      

35
00:02:27,682 --> 00:02:31,483
they paint the stage light's two-part cast-aluminum housing.            

36
00:02:31,485 --> 00:02:33,619
the paint process is electrostatic.        

37
00:02:33,621 --> 00:02:36,756
this means the housing and the black powder paint    

38
00:02:36,758 --> 00:02:40,893
are laced with opposing electrical charges.       

39
00:02:40,895 --> 00:02:44,029
this spreads the paint evenly over the housing.     

40
00:02:44,031 --> 00:02:45,965
then, the housing goes through an oven,      

41
00:02:45,967 --> 00:02:47,600
which bakes on the paint.    

42
00:02:50,905 --> 00:02:52,438
back in the assembly area,    

43
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:56,041
workers install the stage    
light's electronic components,  

44
00:02:56,043 --> 00:02:59,111
starting with the lcd screen.  

45
00:02:59,113 --> 00:03:01,447
it displays the current settings and modes            

46
00:03:01,449 --> 00:03:05,785
and the menus for changing them.              

47
00:03:05,787 --> 00:03:09,321
after covering the screen with a protective plastic shield,   

48
00:03:09,323 --> 00:03:11,990
they install the control panel.             

49
00:03:11,992 --> 00:03:15,327
it has an opening for the screen.         

50
00:03:15,329 --> 00:03:20,265
this plastic cover protects the lcd.        

51
00:03:20,267 --> 00:03:22,001
it also directs outside air   

52
00:03:22,003 --> 00:03:24,136
into the housing to the light's cooling fan,   

53
00:03:24,138 --> 00:03:28,908
which they now secure in place with this bracket.        

54
00:03:28,910 --> 00:03:32,478
the fan dissipates the heat the l.e.d.s generate.      

55
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:37,082
this block of aluminum, called the heat sink, absorbs  

56
00:03:37,084 --> 00:03:41,020
and quickly dissipates some of that heat.        

57
00:03:41,022 --> 00:03:42,421
they mount the l.e.d. array   

58
00:03:42,423 --> 00:03:45,690
on top of this twofold cooling system.     

59
00:03:45,692 --> 00:03:48,094
then, they install the optic assembly.            

60
00:03:48,096 --> 00:03:54,033
this plastic component focuses the individual l.e.d.s.            

61
00:03:54,035 --> 00:03:57,169
they construct         
the stage light's mixing tube,  

62
00:03:57,171 --> 00:03:58,370
lining its interior       

63
00:03:58,372 --> 00:04:02,708
with adhesive-backed aluminum mirrors.        

64
00:04:02,710 --> 00:04:05,110
the mirrors mix the seven l.e.d. colors     

65
00:04:05,112 --> 00:04:06,912
into a single color.       

66
00:04:10,985 --> 00:04:14,119
the assemblers now join the two halves of the mixing tube,    

67
00:04:14,121 --> 00:04:16,989
adding a glass lens on the front.          

68
00:04:16,991 --> 00:04:18,790
the lens focuses the light    

69
00:04:18,792 --> 00:04:22,228
produced by the 60 l.e.d.s into a single beam.       

70
00:04:24,265 --> 00:04:27,099
then, they install the tube over the optic.         

71
00:04:30,604 --> 00:04:32,537
next, they mount the control card   

72
00:04:32,539 --> 00:04:35,274
to the side of the mixing tube.              

73
00:04:35,276 --> 00:04:39,678
the control card is the stage light's onboard computer.            

74
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:43,481
it processes the commands the lighting technician enters.             

75
00:04:43,483 --> 00:04:45,750
commands can be entered from the control panel      

76
00:04:45,752 --> 00:04:49,822
or remotely from a computer.   

77
00:04:49,824 --> 00:04:52,158
after installing the main power supply,      

78
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:55,494
they plug a dmx cable into the control card.      

79
00:04:57,832 --> 00:04:59,965
dmx is the digital network    

80
00:04:59,967 --> 00:05:01,901
through which the console or computer           

81
00:05:01,903 --> 00:05:05,638
communicates to the stage light.             

82
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:08,774
they join this completed unit to the rest of the housing,   

83
00:05:08,776 --> 00:05:11,877
which has the dmx and power connectors.      

84
00:05:14,448 --> 00:05:16,649
this stage light is now finished            

85
00:05:16,651 --> 00:05:19,784
and ready for a thorough quality control check.      

86
00:05:19,786 --> 00:05:21,987
they plug it into a testing machine,     

87
00:05:21,989 --> 00:05:26,191
which powers it up and verifies several functions.           

88
00:05:26,193 --> 00:05:28,593
the machine also calibrates every color      

89
00:05:28,595 --> 00:05:34,132
to ensure consistency in every stage light they manufacture.  

90
00:05:34,134 --> 00:05:36,535
then, they run the stage light at full power          

91
00:05:36,537 --> 00:05:38,470
for three hours nonstop     

92
00:05:38,472 --> 00:05:43,342
to simulate strenuous operating conditions.      

93
00:05:43,344 --> 00:05:45,344
once the light passes these tests,       

94
00:05:45,346 --> 00:05:48,781
it's ready for its stage debut.             

